reviews.review_text: We came here whilst on holiday in the Cotswolds & I have to say we were really pleased to have found this place. We had a great evening with live music, great cider & wonderful food from the Filipino kitchen. A lovely atmosphere. There's a good selection of different food kitchens available including pizza, India, burgers etc. The bar serves a good amount of different ciders & their own shop sells all kinds of lovely food to take away. If we come to the area again we will definitely look forward to visiting again. Such a great idea that more places should have!
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you for such a great review :-)

text.en: Thank you for such a great review :-)

reviews.review_text: Visited over the weekend for the first time. Nice vibe with a variety of quality food outlets to eat from, all of which were local producers. Great range of ciders to drink if you like that, very limited on the beer front, though to be fair it is a cider venue! Large deli shop selling a variety of (not the cheapest) goods, again with an emphasis on local.

reviews.review_text: What an amazing venue!!! The street food is incredible and the atmosphere is amazing. The variety of food options and the quality of food is top notch. The only criticism is the state of the gents toilets which I found quite disgusting tbh and this was at 2pm on a Monday afternoon. The floor was drenched and they were not particularly clean. This really needs to be addressed and soon.

reviews.review_text: Came here Sunday for breakfast at the Woozy Pig. Lovely breakfast. Massive grounds and a lot more there then id expected in respect to eateries. They all seem to work with each other well to, the Woozy Pig doesnt serve drinks but you can get them from the bakery or the bar. Farm shop is a good size lots of produce. Great atmosphere very chilled vibes (at 1030-1045am)

Wide selection of beer and cider but a shame all but one cider is over 6% abv and given the location it means taxi home. Hoping they‚Äôll get a few ‚Äòsession ciders‚Äô for the summer.
Great little shop too serving deli items such as breads, cheeses, pies etc.
Advertises movies, bands, quizzes etc that take place monthly. Children welcome, dogs welcome. Would recommend popping in if you‚Äôre that side of cheltenham

reviews.review_text:
What a great venue, amazing staff, amazing drink & food.

Have to make a special shoutout to the staff, they are always working hard when it is busy. Service with a smile.

Went to an event and it was exceptional, sound quality was on point. Really was a great sonic experience.

Great atmosphere around the venue, beautifully decorated.

Would recommend to everyone, suitable for all ages.

reviews.review_text: Parking is plentiful.  Good choice of food outlets. Our food from Ja ho? was very good.  Dropped 1 star as it was a very long wait to get to the bar, apparently due to holding a private function also. Perhaps that should have been addressed prior to opening. We left after 1 drink as the queue at the bar was around 12 people deep, could have waited 30 minutes or more to be served.

reviews.review_text:
A lovely place to visit in Cheltenham/The Cotswolds, great choices of food/drink with several food truck style pop ups plus the on site bakery & farm shop is amazing.

The atmosphere is relaxed, country & yet elegant at the same time. It‚Äôs a great mix which just works & we enjoy every visit. It gets very busy on a weekend as it‚Äôs one of the places to go for a catch up with friends or family or even take the dog.

Very family friendly with baby change facilities as well, we‚Äôve taken our little one a lot & you don‚Äôt need to worry about them making noise as there‚Äôs such a buzz around anyway.
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you so much for taking the time to review. See you on site soon!

reviews.review_text:
Brilliant place! Always a great vibe, lots going on, fantastic live entertainment and a great food selection. We've been there sooo many times and had lots of fun every time!
The Humble Kusina is the best place to eat serving fresh Filipino food.
We had it countless of times and never had a bad serving.
Koloshi is another great one, serving delicious curry dishes.  I found the food absolutely fantastic and the people working the extremely lovely and accommodating.
Woozy pig was my least favourite ( we did  only get dirty fries so maybe the popularity of it is based on the burgers)
They were OK, but I found they were super pricey for what you got ( a load of fries and not a lot of toppings). It didnt help that shortly after I got mine, my partner got his dirty fries from Humble Kusina and oh my word the difference!!!! His were packed with fresh, colourful toppings and delicious crispy duck ( my mouth is watering so much writing this!!!!!!)
Whilst mine were just well... fries.. as at that point I run out of the ones covered in the toppings üò©

But despite that, I still absolutely love the place
It is great for literally everyone!
There's lots of doggies, great for kids, we bring our little boy with us, he loves it. lots of young people but all other age groups too. It really is super versatile
Come check it out! Grab a quick bite or a drink. Cider is absolutely outstanding here!
Highly recommended! üëçü•∞üëç
reviews.business_response_text: We're delighted to know that you enjoyed your time with us! Rest assured, we will pass on all food feedback to the food vendors. Thank you again for your positive review!

reviews.review_text: If you want normal take away food but want to remortgage to pay for it, this is the place for you. Toilets were absolutely disgusting, urine all over the floor, like cheap night club toilets. Bar staff were friendly, but the people in the food stalls seemed annoyed that you wanted their attention to order... With all the money they're making, invest in air-conditioning as it was 10 million degrees inside. Aimed at the pretentious wanna-be rich.
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you for taking the time to review us. We are addressing the issues you have raised. Should you wish to speak to somebody please e-mail us. :-)

reviews.review_text:
It's changed so much and will be changing more and getting bigger. Not necessarily a good thing in my opinion. On a hot day there was precious little shade apart from inside which was hot from the food prep and being so enclosed.
The food on offer is a good variety of street food and freshly prepared.
Advice would be to get there early as it gets uncomfortably busy in the Summer

reviews.review_text: A really excellent social space - wide range of food offerings and lots of seating inside and out. Appeals to all age ranges - young families, groups, couples - a great space to enjoy the outdoors. Holland Cooper shopping experience is lovely, although they need not to judge people too quickly as they come through the door- appearance is not everything. I could spend all day and quite a bit of money in there, my adult daughter who also has good spending ability felt very uncomfortable and was in and out within minutes - not everyone is the 'Cheltenham' set.
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you for taking the time to write a review, we really appreciate it and will hopefully see you on site again soon.
